WEBVTT

00:04.917 --> 00:06.136
PREVIOUSLY ON
"PUSHING DAISIES"...

00:06.180 --> 00:08.660
Narrator:
YOUNG NED HAD A SPECIAL GIFT.

00:08.704 --> 00:11.011
HE COULD TOUCH DEAD THINGS
AND BRING THEM BACK TO LIFE.

00:11.054 --> 00:14.101
BUT HE COULD ONLY BRING THE DEAD
BACK TO LIFE FOR ONE MINUTE.

00:14.144 --> 00:17.017
[ DING ]ANY LONGER,
AND SOMEONE ELSE HAD TO DIE.

00:17.060 --> 00:20.020
AND THERE WAS ONE MORE THING
HE HAD TO LEARN --

00:20.063 --> 00:21.282
FIRST TOUCH, LIFE.

00:21.325 --> 00:24.154
SECOND TOUCH,
DEAD AGAIN FOREVER.

00:24.198 --> 00:26.548
BUT AS YOUNG NED GREW
INTO THE PIE MAKER,

00:26.591 --> 00:29.681
THIS GIFT PROVED TO BE MOST
USEFUL IN THE UNTIMELY DEATH

00:29.725 --> 00:31.770
OF HIS CHILDHOOD SWEETHEART,
CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

00:31.814 --> 00:33.120
Emerson:
ARE YOU IN LOVE WITH HER?

00:33.163 --> 00:34.599
YOU ONLY GOT A MINUTE.I KNOW.

00:34.643 --> 00:35.948
60 SECONDS.
I KNOW.

00:35.992 --> 00:37.602
WHAT IF YOU
DIDN'T HAVE TO BE DEAD?

00:37.646 --> 00:39.952
YOU CAN'T TOUCH ME.SO A KISS IS
OUT OF THE QUESTION?

00:39.996 --> 00:42.868
Chuck:
YOU TOUCH MURDER VICTIMS,
YOU ASK WHO KILLED THEM,

00:42.912 --> 00:44.653
YOU TOUCH THEM AGAIN,
THEY GO BACK TO BEING DEAD,

00:44.696 --> 00:46.133
AND THEN
YOU COLLECT THE REWARD?

00:46.176 --> 00:49.136
THAT'S IT IN A NUTSHELL.

00:49.179 --> 00:50.659
MIGHT I MAKE
AN OBSERVATION?

00:50.702 --> 00:51.834
COMPLIMENT OR CRITICISM?

00:51.877 --> 00:53.401
A NEUTRAL THOUGHT,
I WOULD SAY.

00:53.444 --> 00:54.924
IT'S NEITHER COMPLIMENTARY
NOR CRITICAL.

00:54.967 --> 00:56.839
NEUTRAL THOUGHT
GIVES ME PAUSE.

00:56.882 --> 00:59.581
YOU SEEM DECIDEDLY UNHAPPY.WHAT ARE YOU BEATING AT?

00:59.624 --> 01:01.670
AN OFFER TO REPAIR
YOUR ESPRESSO MACHINE.

01:11.854 --> 01:14.074
Narrator: THE MOTTO OF
THE LONGBOROUGH SCHOOL FOR BOYS

01:14.117 --> 01:17.642
WAS "INSTITUTUM
SUPERIOR OMNIBUS,"

01:17.686 --> 01:19.688
OR "TRADITION OVER ALL."

01:19.731 --> 01:23.170
BUT ON THIS MORNING, WHETHER
IT WAS THE TOPIC OF FLIGHT

01:23.213 --> 01:25.824
OR THE BRANDY
IN THE TEACHERS PARLOR,

01:25.868 --> 01:28.262
MR. GAULT THREW TRADITION
TO THE WIND

01:28.305 --> 01:31.700
AND LET THE STUDENTS CHOOSE
THEIR OWN LAB PARTNERS.

01:31.743 --> 01:36.531
YOUNG NED, HOWEVER,
FOUND HIS CHOSEN FORHIM.

01:36.574 --> 01:39.838
EUGENE MULCHANDANI
WAS AN EXCHANGE STUDENT

01:39.882 --> 01:41.971
FROM GORAKHPUR, INDIA.

01:42.014 --> 01:46.715
YOUNG NED FELT A GNAWING PITY
GROWING IN HIS STOMACH,

01:46.758 --> 01:47.716
AS WAS TRADITION.

01:49.544 --> 01:54.853
BUT BENEATH EUGENE'S HEADGEAR
THRIVED AN ACTIVE IMAGINATION

01:54.897 --> 01:58.553
AND A USEFUL GIFT
FOR AERONAUTICAL MODEL BUILDING,

01:58.596 --> 02:02.165
AS WELL AS THE HOPE THAT
SOMEONE MIGHT NOT DISLIKE HIM

02:02.209 --> 02:04.994
FOR THE SIMPLE FACT
THAT HE WAS DIFFERENT.

02:06.604 --> 02:08.302
[ AIR HISSING ]

02:12.262 --> 02:15.396
YOUNG NED FOUND HIMSELF
BREAKING WITH HIS OWN TRADITION

02:15.439 --> 02:17.485
AND, IN A MOMENT OF PASSION...

02:19.443 --> 02:21.271
...HE FOUGHT BACK.

02:22.142 --> 02:24.927
FOR THE FIRST TIME SINCE
HIS FATHER DROPPED HIM OFF,

02:24.970 --> 02:27.930
YOUNG NED MADE A FRIEND.

02:27.973 --> 02:31.673
IN THE SURGE OF EMOTION,
HE FORGOT HIS MOTHER HAD DIED,

02:31.716 --> 02:33.153
HIS FATHER HAD LEFT HIM,

02:33.196 --> 02:35.938
AND THAT HE MISSED
THE GIRL NAMED CHUCK.

02:35.981 --> 02:39.681
HE ALSO FORGOT HE WAS JUMPING
INTO A PILE OF DEAD LEAVES

02:39.724 --> 02:42.510
THAT WERE ONCE ALIVE.

02:47.602 --> 02:51.301
EUGENE MULCHANDANI FLED
IN A FLURRY OF SALIVA AND FEAR.

02:53.129 --> 02:56.567
EUGENE WOULD EVENTUALLY FORGET
YOUNG NED'S MISTAKE

02:56.611 --> 02:59.179
AND CHALK IT UP TO MAGIC LEAVES.

02:59.222 --> 03:01.224
BUT YOUNG NED WOULD NEVER FORGET

03:01.268 --> 03:06.186
THAT HAPPINESS BORN OF PASSION
IS ALWAYS SHORT-LIVED.

03:06.229 --> 03:08.144
YET, THROUGH NO FAULT
OF HIS OWN,

03:08.188 --> 03:11.016
HE HAD ONCE AGAIN
STUMBLED INTO HAPPINESS...

03:11.060 --> 03:12.235
GOOD MORNING.

03:12.279 --> 03:14.106
Narrator:
...WHICH TERRIFIED HIM.

03:14.150 --> 03:15.760
MORNING.

03:15.804 --> 03:17.371
GUESS WHAT DAY IT IS
TODAY.

03:17.414 --> 03:19.329
WORLD HELLO DAY.

03:19.373 --> 03:22.637
OH! YOU FINALLY PUT UP
MY CALENDAR OF OBSCURE HOLIDAYS.

03:22.680 --> 03:24.856
YES. AND HOLA!

03:24.900 --> 03:26.423
THAT'S ESPAÃ‘OLA.

03:26.467 --> 03:29.687
MERHABA, SELAMAT PAGI,
O SI YO.

03:29.731 --> 03:31.689
THAT'S TURKISH, INDONESIAN,
AND CHEROKEE.

03:31.733 --> 03:33.169
ALTHOUGH THE INDONESIAN
REALLY SAYS "GOOD DAY,"

03:33.213 --> 03:35.171
WHICH I THINK IS MUCH BETTER
THAN "HELLO,"

03:35.215 --> 03:37.129
'CAUSE WHAT DOES THAT SAY?

03:37.173 --> 03:39.044
THAT SAYS, "I'M HERE.
YOUR TURN TO TALK."
KIND OF SELFISH.

03:39.088 --> 03:41.177
[ LAUGHS ]

03:41.221 --> 03:42.874
WHAT?

03:42.918 --> 03:44.528
NOTHING.

03:44.572 --> 03:46.182
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER
WISHED TO EXPRESS TO CHUCK

03:46.226 --> 03:49.141
EXACTLY HOW INTENSE
HIS FEELINGS WERE FOR HER.

03:49.185 --> 03:50.230
AM I YOUR BOYFRIEND?

03:52.014 --> 03:53.624
AND I REALIZE
"BOYFRIEND" AND "GIRLFRIEND"

03:53.668 --> 03:55.235
ARE FAMILIAR,
TRITE LABELS.

03:55.278 --> 03:56.584
IF CONVENTION WERE SOMETHING
YOU SOAKED IN,

03:56.627 --> 03:57.889
"BOYFRIEND" WOULD BE
DRIPPING WITH IT.

03:57.933 --> 03:59.891
BUT WE'VE NEVER
ACTUALLY SAID IT,

03:59.935 --> 04:01.893
AND I THINK WE NEED
TO DEFINE THE RELATIONSHIP.

04:01.937 --> 04:05.245
BUT, UM, IT MAY BE HELPFUL
IN A FAMILIAR, TRITE WAY --

04:05.288 --> 04:07.812
THE WAY ON A HOLIDAY
CREATED TO SELL GREETING CARDS,

04:07.856 --> 04:09.814
IT'S STILL KIND OF NICE
TO GET A CARD.

04:09.858 --> 04:13.253
AND ARE YOU GONNA CUT ME OFF
WITH A "YES" ANYTIME SOON?

04:13.296 --> 04:14.558
YES.

04:14.602 --> 04:15.559
[ SIGHS ]

04:15.603 --> 04:17.082
[ SIGHS ]

04:18.606 --> 04:20.521
[ LAUGHS ]

04:20.564 --> 04:23.741
YOU NEVER SAID
WHAT TODAY IS.

04:23.785 --> 04:25.569
THANK YOU.

04:25.613 --> 04:28.659
TODAY IS
MY DADDY'S BIRTHDAY.

04:30.095 --> 04:32.881
YOU KNOW HE WOULD HAVE BEEN
60 TODAY IF HE WERE STILL ALIVE?

04:32.924 --> 04:35.579
Narrator:
THE MENTION OF CHUCK'S FATHER

04:35.623 --> 04:38.278
SENT THE PIE MAKER'S THOUGHTS
SPINNING.

04:38.321 --> 04:40.584
OH!

04:40.628 --> 04:41.759
WHAT'S WRONG?

04:41.803 --> 04:43.065
NOTHING.

04:43.108 --> 04:45.110
Narrator:
THE MEANING OF "NOTHING" WAS

04:45.154 --> 04:46.547
"I NEVER TOLD YOU

04:46.590 --> 04:49.680
THAT I INADVERTENTLY KILLED
YOUR FATHER."

04:49.724 --> 04:52.292
OLIVE SNOOK
HAD TOLD THE PIE MAKER

04:52.335 --> 04:55.773
SHE WAS HAPPY FOR HIS HAPPINESS
WITH THE GIRL NAMED CHUCK,

04:55.817 --> 04:58.123
BUT UPON HEARING
THE WORD "BOYFRIEND,"

04:58.167 --> 05:01.562
SHE UNEXPECTEDLY FOUND
HER SADNESS SPINNING INTO ANGER.

05:01.605 --> 05:05.957
IT WAS A TRUTH SHE COULD NOT YET
STARE IN THE FACE.

05:06.001 --> 05:07.568
OLIVE.

05:09.396 --> 05:10.527
HUH?

05:10.571 --> 05:12.442
WHERE ARE
ALL THE CUSTOMERS?

05:12.486 --> 05:14.139
YOU GOT ME.

05:14.183 --> 05:15.576
Alfredo:
IAM A CUSTOMER.

05:15.619 --> 05:17.882
Narrator: HER DIZZY HEART
MISSED ANOTHER TRUTH

05:17.926 --> 05:20.407
STARING HER IN THE FACE.

05:20.450 --> 05:21.625
FREDO.

05:21.669 --> 05:22.844
[ BELL RINGS ]

05:24.933 --> 05:26.587
ALFREDO,
WHEN DID YOU COME IN?

05:26.630 --> 05:28.632
BEFORE, WHEN YOU OPENED
THE DOOR FOR ME

05:28.676 --> 05:30.373
AND I ASKED HOW YOU WERE,
THEN YOU SAID YOU WERE FINE.

05:30.417 --> 05:33.333
THEN I ASKED FOR A
MACCHIATO, AND YOU SAID,
"COMING RIGHT UP."

05:33.376 --> 05:35.117
SO, I GUESS
YOU'LL STILL WANT THAT.

05:35.160 --> 05:36.161
YES, PLEASE.

05:41.776 --> 05:43.908
[ METAL CLANKING ]

05:43.952 --> 05:45.649
THIS CASE IS EASY MONEY.

05:45.693 --> 05:46.998
YOU TOLD ME THAT ALREADY.

05:47.042 --> 05:48.478
IT'S MY FAULT
CHUCK'S FATHER'S DEAD.

05:48.522 --> 05:50.132
YOU TOLD ME THAT
ALREADY.

05:50.175 --> 05:51.568
I SHOULD JUST TELL HER.

05:51.612 --> 05:53.570
WELL, THAT IDEA
MIGHT MAKE A STUPIDIDEA

05:53.614 --> 05:54.832
FEEL BETTER ABOUT ITSELF.

05:54.876 --> 05:56.834
I CAN'T KEEP LYING TO HER.

05:56.878 --> 05:58.401
YOU AIN'T LYING.

05:58.445 --> 06:00.142
THE ONLY WAY YOU'RE LYING
IS IF SHE ASKS THE QUESTION,

06:00.185 --> 06:02.013
[ Imitating Chuck ]
"HEY, DID YOU KILL MY FATHER

06:02.057 --> 06:03.537
"WHEN YOU BROUGHT
YOUR MOTHER BACK,

06:03.580 --> 06:05.495
WHICH I DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT,
BECAUSE YOU NEVER TOLD ME?"

06:05.539 --> 06:06.888
[ Normal voice ]
DON'T TELL HER.

06:09.891 --> 06:11.588
HEY.
HAVE YOU GUYS HEARD?

06:11.632 --> 06:14.199
THE MOST AMAZING NEW CANDY STORE
IS OPENING UP ACROSS THE STREET.

06:14.243 --> 06:15.331
IT'S AMAZING.

06:16.419 --> 06:18.421
WHO ARE YOU?

06:18.465 --> 06:20.510
I'M JUST SOME GUY WHO'S
TELLING EVERYBODY ABOUT IT
'CAUSE IT'S SO AMAZING.

06:20.554 --> 06:22.686
SERIOUSLY, EVERYBODY,
YOU GOT TO CHECK THIS OUT.

06:22.730 --> 06:24.209
DO YOU WORK
FOR THE CANDY STORE?

06:24.253 --> 06:26.342
NO.
I'M JUST SOME GUY.

06:26.386 --> 06:27.561
"SOME GUY"?

06:27.604 --> 06:29.650
YEAH. SOME GUY
WHO SURE LOVES CANDY.

06:29.693 --> 06:32.348
BE SURE TO TELL
EVERYONE YOU KNOW. SEE YA.

06:32.392 --> 06:35.003
OH, NO.
SEE? THIS IS HOW IT ALL ENDS.

06:35.046 --> 06:37.440
SOME WEIRD GUY COMES IN SAYING
STUFF THAT DON'T MAKE NO SENSE.

06:37.484 --> 06:38.920
AND BY THE TIME
YOUR HEAD REALIZES,

06:38.963 --> 06:40.704
"HEY, THIS WEIRD GUY
DON'T MAKE NO SENSE,"

06:40.748 --> 06:42.184
YOUR GUTS ARE
ALL OVER THE WINDOW.

06:42.227 --> 06:44.055
HERE.

06:44.099 --> 06:45.666
SO, DID NED TELL YOU
HE'S MY BOYFRIEND?

06:47.581 --> 06:48.712
[ LAUGHS ] YEAH.

06:48.756 --> 06:50.584
YOU TWO ARE GONNA LOVE
THIS CASE.

06:50.627 --> 06:52.455
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

06:52.499 --> 06:54.109
ONE TONY DiNAPOLI --

06:54.152 --> 06:57.504
26 YEARS, 9 WEEKS, 2 HOURS,
AND 10 MINUTES OLD --

06:57.547 --> 07:00.724
WAS FOUND STRANGLED TO DEATH
IN HIS FRIEND'S APARTMENT.

07:00.768 --> 07:04.424
HIS GIRLFRIEND, TINA ARONGINO,
WAS ARRESTED AT THE SCENE

07:04.467 --> 07:06.208
FOR THE MURDER
THE POLICE DESCRIBED

07:06.251 --> 07:08.906
AS A TYPICAL CRIME OF PASSION.

07:08.950 --> 07:10.473
I FREAKIN' LOVED TONY.

07:10.517 --> 07:13.215
YOU GOT TO HELP ME, EMERSON COD.
I DIDN'T DO IT.

07:14.608 --> 07:17.828
Narrator: WITH THE EVIDENCE
STACKED AGAINST HER,

07:17.872 --> 07:21.310
TINA ARONGINO HIRED EMERSON COD.

07:22.877 --> 07:24.139
[ WATCH TICKING ]

07:25.227 --> 07:26.446
[ BOTH GASP ]

07:26.489 --> 07:28.535
[ CHUCKLES ]
HOW YOU DOIN'?

07:28.578 --> 07:30.928
UH, DO YOU KNOW
HOW YOU'REDOING?

07:30.972 --> 07:32.277
I'M DEAD, RIGHT?

07:32.321 --> 07:34.236
YOUR GIRLFRIEND MURDER YOU?

07:34.279 --> 07:36.238
HELL, NO. ME AND TINA
WERE MAD FOR EACH OTHER.

07:36.281 --> 07:37.718
SHE FRIGGIN' LOVED ME.

07:37.761 --> 07:40.460
IT WAS BURLY BRUCE CARTER
WHO STRANGLED ME.

07:40.503 --> 07:43.593
THIS BURLY BRUCE, DID HE HAVE
CONGENITALLY DAINTY HANDS?

07:43.637 --> 07:46.074
'CAUSE THOSE STRANGLE MARKS
WERE MADE BY A PETITE FEMALE

07:46.117 --> 07:48.946
WITH ROUNDED, CRIMSON,
FRENCH-TIPPED NAILS.

07:48.990 --> 07:50.774
HE USED HIS GIRLFRIEND'S HANDS
TO KILL ME.

07:50.818 --> 07:53.037
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH THAT.

07:53.081 --> 07:56.780
HIS GIRLFRIEND'S A DOLL --
NOT LIKE YOU'REA DOLL.

07:56.824 --> 07:59.479
SHE'S A DOLLDOLL,
LIKE LIFE-SIZED AND PLASTIC.

07:59.522 --> 08:00.784
YOU MEAN SHE'S NOT REAL?

08:00.828 --> 08:01.959
DON'T TELL BRUCE THAT.

08:02.003 --> 08:03.526
THAT WAS MY MISTAKE.

08:03.570 --> 08:06.050
BRUCE INVITED ME AND TINA OVER
FOR A DOUBLE DATE.

08:06.094 --> 08:08.618
I GOT TO BRUCE'S PLACE
BEFORE TINA DID.

08:08.662 --> 08:11.142
WHEN HE SHOWED ME THE DOLL
AND SAID IT WAS HIS GIRLFRIEND,

08:11.186 --> 08:12.970
I LET HIM HAVE IT.

08:13.014 --> 08:14.450
THEN HE KIND OF FLIPPED OUT.

08:17.018 --> 08:19.150
[ CHOKING ]

08:19.194 --> 08:22.110
SO YOU'RE SAYING
THE MURDER WEAPON WAS
A LIFE-SIZE-HUMAN DOLL?

08:22.153 --> 08:23.546
THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYIN'.

08:23.590 --> 08:24.765
GOT A PHONE NUMBER,
SWEETIE?

08:24.808 --> 08:26.984
DO YOU MIND?
WHAT ABOUT FRIGGIN' TINA?

08:27.028 --> 08:28.246
I'M DEAD, AIN'T I?

08:28.290 --> 08:29.334
NO.

08:30.379 --> 08:31.598
NOWYOU'RE DEAD.

08:31.641 --> 08:33.077
OH, MY GOSH.

08:33.121 --> 08:34.557
WELL, THATWAS
A CRIME OF PASSION.

08:34.601 --> 08:36.907
WHAT? IT WAS A MINUTE.
I'M HAVING A HARD DAY.

08:36.951 --> 08:38.039
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:41.651 --> 08:43.610
Narrator:
OLIVE FOUND HERSELF IN A CLOUD

08:43.653 --> 08:45.960
OF STEAMED MILK AND SELF-PITY,

08:46.003 --> 08:47.788
UNAWARE OF THE WARM BREATH

08:47.831 --> 08:50.138
BLOWING OUT OF THE MOUTH
OF ALFREDO ALDARISIO.

08:50.181 --> 08:53.141
[ ESPRESSO MACHINE HISSING ]...IS COMPROMISED,
BECAUSE A TRAVELING SALESMAN

08:53.184 --> 08:54.795
ISN'T SUCH A THING
IF HE DOES NOT TRAVEL.

08:54.838 --> 08:56.753
AS ANY NONTRADITIONAL-REMEDY
SALESMAN KNOWS,

08:56.797 --> 08:58.799
RESISTANCE TO THE NOVEL
AND THE UNCONVENTIONAL

08:58.842 --> 09:00.757
IS MARBLED THROUGH THIS COUNTRY
LIKE GRISTLE.

09:00.801 --> 09:03.151
IF I'M NOT CUTTING THAT GRISTLE,
I'M NOT DOING MY JOB.

09:03.194 --> 09:04.892
[ HISSING STOPS ]

09:04.935 --> 09:06.328
WERE YOU TALKING?

09:06.371 --> 09:08.286
I HAVE TO GO BACK
ON THE ROAD SOON.

09:08.330 --> 09:10.332
IT MAY BE A LONG TIME
BEFORE I RETURN.

09:10.375 --> 09:11.986
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

09:12.029 --> 09:13.727
OF COURSE.

09:15.337 --> 09:17.600
IF YOU LOVED ME...

09:17.644 --> 09:18.906
YES.

09:18.949 --> 09:20.342
...AND WE COULD NEVER, EVER,
EVER TOUCH,

09:20.385 --> 09:21.996
WOULDN'T YOU EVENTUALLY
GET OVER IT AND MOVE ON,

09:22.039 --> 09:23.824
LETTING SOMEONE ELSE
HAVE THE SLIGHTEST HOPE

09:23.867 --> 09:25.173
THAT YOU MIGHT MOVE ON
TO THEM?

09:25.216 --> 09:26.783
IF I LOVED YOU?

09:26.827 --> 09:28.089
YEAH.

09:30.831 --> 09:33.877
THEN I WOULD LOVE YOU
IN ANY WAY I COULD.

09:33.921 --> 09:35.836
AND IF WE COULD NOT TOUCH,

09:35.879 --> 09:38.621
THEN I WOULD DRAW STRENGTH
FROM YOUR BEAUTY.

09:38.665 --> 09:40.144
AND IF I WENT BLIND,

09:40.188 --> 09:43.539
THEN I WOULD FILL MY SOUL
WITH THE SOUND OF YOUR VOICE

09:43.583 --> 09:45.976
AND THE CONTENTS
OF YOUR THOUGHTS

09:46.020 --> 09:48.500
UNTIL THE LAST SPARK
OF MY LOVE FOR YOU

09:48.544 --> 09:51.242
LIT THE SHABBY DARKNESS
OF MY DYING MIND.

09:53.636 --> 09:55.290
EH, FORGET IT.

09:59.207 --> 10:02.645
MR. CARTER?
MR. BRUCE CARTER?

10:02.689 --> 10:05.039
WHAT IF HE DOES ACTUALLY
BELIEVE THAT HIS DOLL
IS A REAL PERSON?

10:05.082 --> 10:07.694
MAYBE THAT IS HIS TRUTH.
IT'S JUST DIFFERENT
FROM OURTRUTH.

10:07.737 --> 10:09.478
THE TRUTH
AIN'T LIKE PUPPIES --

10:09.521 --> 10:12.002
A BUNCH OF THEM RUNNING AROUND,
YOU PICK YOUR FAVORITE.

10:12.046 --> 10:14.004
ONETRUTH,
AND IT HAS COME A-KNOCKIN'.

10:14.048 --> 10:15.440
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

10:15.484 --> 10:16.703
BUT LET'S JUST SAY
HE'S GOT HIS OWN TRUTH,

10:16.746 --> 10:18.705
AND HE'S GROWN ATTACHED
TO IT.

10:18.748 --> 10:20.663
MARRY THAT WITH A SHORT FUSE
AND A VIOLENT TEMPER,
AND WHAT YOU GET IS --

10:20.707 --> 10:21.664
[ DOOR OPENS ]

10:23.492 --> 10:25.886
WHAT DO YOUWANT?

10:25.929 --> 10:28.062
THAT CRAZY BROAD TINA
TRYIN' TO PIN THIS ON ME?

10:28.105 --> 10:29.498
'CAUSE SHE CAME IN
SCREAMIN',

10:29.541 --> 10:31.413
SAID TONY HAD BEEN
FOOLIN' AROUND ON HER.

10:31.456 --> 10:33.067
THEN SHE LEAPT ON HIM
LIKE A CAT.

10:33.110 --> 10:35.722
IT WAS OVER BEFORE IT STARTED.
THE EVIDENCE BACKS ME UP.

10:35.765 --> 10:37.114
YEAH.
ON THAT SUBJECT --

10:37.158 --> 10:38.855
MR. CARTER, YOU ARE
A BIG, TOUGH GUY,

10:38.899 --> 10:40.683
AND I HAVE NO DOUBT
YOU COULD MAKE MINCEMEAT
OUT OF ALL OF US

10:40.727 --> 10:42.424
IF WHAT YOU NEEDED
WAS MORE MINCEMEAT.

10:42.467 --> 10:44.861
BUT THE SHOES BY THE DOOR
AND THE DAFFODILS ON THE TABLE

10:44.905 --> 10:47.342
AND THE SMELL OF GARLIC PASTA
COMING FROM THE KITCHEN...

10:47.385 --> 10:50.867
MAYBE I GOT A GIRLFRIEND.
THAT SO HARD TO BELIEVE?

10:50.911 --> 10:53.174
AND SHEILA'S GOT
NOTHIN' TO DO WITH THIS.

10:53.217 --> 10:55.089
YEAH. UH,
WHEN YOU SAY "SHEILA" --

10:55.132 --> 10:57.744
DID SHEILA WITNESS THE MURDER
OF TONY DiNAPOLI?

10:57.787 --> 11:00.616
I'M DONE TALKIN'.
YOUSE NEED TO LEAVE NOW.

11:00.660 --> 11:03.619
BUT IF SHE SAW SOMETHING
OR DID SOMETHING, WE UNDERSTAND.

11:03.663 --> 11:05.577
YOU'RE JUST TRYING TO PROTECT
HER 'CAUSE YOU LOVE HER.

11:09.407 --> 11:12.280
IT WASN'T SHEILA'S FAULT,
OKAY?

11:12.323 --> 11:13.760
IT WAS MINE.

11:13.803 --> 11:15.457
TAKE ME.

11:15.500 --> 11:19.113
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE PUT HER
IN THAT SITUATION.

11:19.156 --> 11:20.331
Chuck:
IT'S OKAY. OKAY.

11:20.375 --> 11:22.856
SHEILA! SHEILA, BABY!

11:22.899 --> 11:24.248
YOU CAN COME OUT.

11:26.207 --> 11:27.338
THE JIG'S UP.

11:27.382 --> 11:28.557
[ CRYING ]

11:28.600 --> 11:30.515
IT'S OKAY.
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH.

11:30.559 --> 11:31.691
SHE'S PROBABLY
TOO SCARED.

11:31.734 --> 11:33.301
MM-HMM.

11:33.344 --> 11:35.738
Narrator: THE INFORMATION
EMERSON COD GAVE THE POLICE

11:35.782 --> 11:37.609
LED TO FURTHER INVESTIGATION

11:37.653 --> 11:42.876
OF TONY DiNAPOLI'S REAL MURDER
DUE TO UNREAL CIRCUMSTANCES.

11:42.919 --> 11:45.617
TINA ARONGINO WAS RELEASED.

11:45.661 --> 11:49.317
BURLY BRUCE CARTER WAS DETAINED
BY LOCAL AUTHORITIES,

11:49.360 --> 11:50.753
AWAITING HIS TRIAL.

11:50.797 --> 11:52.450
SHEILA!

11:52.494 --> 11:54.148
I LOVE YOU!

11:54.191 --> 11:58.500
Narrator: SHEILA THE DOLL
WAS ALSO DETAINED.

11:58.543 --> 12:00.067
OLIVE, HAVING BEEN DETAINED

12:00.110 --> 12:02.547
BY HER OWN ANGRY THOUGHTS
FOR LONG ENOUGH,

12:02.591 --> 12:06.203
HAD ESCAPED
TO SAMPLE SOMETHING SWEETER.

12:16.083 --> 12:17.780
WELCOME.
BITTER MUCH?

12:17.824 --> 12:19.303
I'M SORRY?

12:19.347 --> 12:21.523
SWEETS TASTE SWEETER
WITH A BITE OF THE BITTER.

12:21.566 --> 12:24.178
WELCOME TO BALSAM'S BITTERSWEETS
TAFFY & SWEETS EMPORIUM.

12:24.221 --> 12:25.919
BITTER MUCH?

12:25.962 --> 12:28.225
YES. ACTUALLY,
BITTER VERYMUCH.

12:28.269 --> 12:29.923
AREN'T YOU "SOME GUY"?

12:29.966 --> 12:31.707
YOU'RE A PIE HOLER.

12:31.751 --> 12:33.187
BILLY BALSAM, CO-OWNER.

12:33.230 --> 12:34.362
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]

12:34.405 --> 12:36.190
Chuck: HI.

12:36.233 --> 12:38.932
I-I THOUGHT WE SHOULD BRING PIE.
THAT'S WHAT NEW NEIGHBORS DO.

12:38.975 --> 12:40.716
SO SWEET.
YOU ARE SO SWEET.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.718
A GIRL COULD GET THE DIABETES
JUST STANDING NEXT TO YOU.

12:42.762 --> 12:46.200
DILLY, THERE'S SOME OTHER
SMALL-BUSINESS OWNERS FROM
ACROSS THE STREET.

12:46.243 --> 12:47.810
WHO'S DILLY?

12:47.854 --> 12:49.246
[ DOOR OPENS ]

12:50.944 --> 12:52.293
BITTER MUCH?

12:52.336 --> 12:54.469
PIE HOLERS, I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET MY SISTER

12:54.512 --> 12:55.992
AND THE QUEEN OF CANDY,
DILLY BALSAM.

12:56.036 --> 12:57.733
IT'S A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.
DILLY BALSAM.

12:57.777 --> 12:58.734
HI.

12:58.778 --> 13:00.562
HI. I'M NED.

13:00.605 --> 13:02.607
HE'S THE LORD
OF THE PIES.

13:04.131 --> 13:05.741
OH, OF COURSE!

13:05.785 --> 13:08.309
THAT LITTLE PIE PLACE
WITH THE QUAINT CRUST ROOF.

13:08.352 --> 13:11.573
I DO HOPE BILLY APOLOGIZED
FOR ALL THIS COMMOTION TODAY.

13:11.616 --> 13:13.967
IF BY "APOLOGIZED,"
YOU MEAN HE PRETENDED
TO BE SOMEBODY HE'S NOT

13:14.010 --> 13:16.491
SO HE COULD LURE US
INTO YOUR SUGAR SHACK...

13:16.534 --> 13:18.058
ACTUALLY,
I THINK IT'S REALLY NICE

13:18.101 --> 13:19.363
TO HAVE A BIT OF EXCITEMENT
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

13:19.407 --> 13:20.843
I'M SO GLAD
YOU SEE IT THAT WAY.

13:23.890 --> 13:25.674
DO YOU LIKE EXCITEMENT,
PIE MAN?

13:25.717 --> 13:27.894
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER
DID NOT LIKE EXCITEMENT,

13:27.937 --> 13:30.897
BUT HE KNEW TO BE POLITE
TO A NEW NEIGHBOR.

13:30.940 --> 13:33.247
I FEEL EXCITEMENT IS SO MUCH
BETTER THAN A LOT OF THINGS.

13:33.290 --> 13:34.596
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT I FIND EXCITING?

13:34.639 --> 13:36.163
HUH?

13:36.206 --> 13:39.253
COM...PE...TI...TION.

13:39.296 --> 13:42.778
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT AFRAID
OF A LITTLE COMPETITION.

13:42.822 --> 13:45.346
I DON'T REALLY SEE US
AS COMPETITORS.

13:46.303 --> 13:48.871
IS WHAT'S IN THAT BOX
THE AMAZING SMELL I'M SMELLING?

13:48.915 --> 13:51.352
Chuck: OH, IS WHAT YOU'RE
SMELLING GEORGIA PEACH COBBLER?THAT'S EXACTLY IT.

13:51.395 --> 13:53.093
THEN I'M THE GUILTY
GEORGIA PEACH.

13:53.136 --> 13:56.183
IT'S FROM THE PIE HOLE,
ACROSS THE STREET,
AS IN "SHUT YOUR,"

13:56.226 --> 13:58.750
BUT ONE SWEET WHIFF,
AND PEOPLE USUALLY WANT
TO "OPEN THEIR."

13:58.794 --> 14:01.449
THAT SOUNDS DELICIOUS.
LET'S GO.

14:01.492 --> 14:02.624
OH. UM...

14:02.667 --> 14:03.712
BYE.

14:03.755 --> 14:05.366
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

14:06.802 --> 14:08.195
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]

14:08.238 --> 14:09.457
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

14:09.500 --> 14:11.763
I'M SORRY. UM...

14:11.807 --> 14:14.201
THIS IS FOR YOU.
HAPPY GRAND OPENING.

14:14.244 --> 14:16.681
HMM.
THAT WAS INTERESTING.

14:16.725 --> 14:19.946
I ADMIRE
YOUR S-S-S-S-S-S-STRATEGY.

14:19.989 --> 14:21.469
STRATEGY?

14:21.512 --> 14:23.471
SORRY. MY SISTER STUTTERS
WHEN SHE'S UPSET.

14:23.514 --> 14:25.255
WHY IS SHE UPSET?
WHY ARE YOU UPSET?

14:25.299 --> 14:27.954
PRETTY NERVY BRINGING YOUR
P-P-PIE UP IN ALL MY BUSINESS,

14:27.997 --> 14:29.477
STEALING
MY C-C-C-CUSTOMERS.

14:29.520 --> 14:31.392
OH, I-I THINK
THIS IS A MISUNDERSTANDING.

14:31.435 --> 14:33.568
IF YOU WANT A W-W-WAR,
THEN THAT'S WHAT YOU'LL GET.

14:33.611 --> 14:35.744
A WAR? NO.
A WAR'S WHAT WE DON'TWANT.

14:35.787 --> 14:37.659
WE JUST CAME BY
TO SAY H-H-HELLO.

14:37.702 --> 14:39.922
ARE YOU MAKING F-F-F-FUN
OF ME?

14:39.966 --> 14:41.663
SHE'S EAKING OUT-FRAY.

14:41.706 --> 14:43.447
WHAT?
Freaking out.

14:44.666 --> 14:46.059
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN ANYTHING.

14:46.102 --> 14:47.625
AME ON-G-G-G-GAY.

14:47.669 --> 14:48.931
WHAT?

14:48.975 --> 14:50.237
GAME ON.
GAME ON.

14:50.280 --> 14:52.500
GAME ON?GAME ON! NOW GET OUT!

14:52.543 --> 14:53.980
OH!
OH!

14:54.023 --> 14:55.068
[ SCOFFS ]

14:55.111 --> 14:56.504
OUT.

14:56.547 --> 14:57.897
I --

15:03.554 --> 15:05.382
THAT SHOULD
SHAKE THEM UP.

15:05.426 --> 15:09.169
I LIKED THE STUTTERING.
IT WAS OFF-PUTTING AND ODD.

15:09.212 --> 15:10.648
AMATEURS.

15:10.692 --> 15:12.955
WE'LL HAVE THEM
OUT OF BUSINESS IN A WEEK.

15:35.760 --> 15:38.111
YOU STILL THINK
IT'S A COINCIDENCE?

15:38.154 --> 15:40.504
I DON'T THINK SOMEONE
PURPOSELY DAMAGED OUR SIGN

15:40.548 --> 15:42.332
TO READ..."PIE HO."

15:42.376 --> 15:43.812
[ SNORTS ]

15:43.855 --> 15:46.510
HELLO. THAT CRAZY CANDY LADY
THREATENED US.

15:46.554 --> 15:48.599
THEY'RE TRYING TO STEAL
ALL OF OUR BUSINESS.

15:48.643 --> 15:50.253
We've only had
one customer today.

15:50.297 --> 15:52.081
WE CAN'T JUST SIT HERE
AND DO NOTHING.

15:52.125 --> 15:53.082
YES, WE CAN.

15:53.126 --> 15:54.779
CANDY MIGHT BE SWEET,

15:54.823 --> 15:56.172
BUT IT'S A TRAVELING CARNIVAL
BLOWING THROUGH TOWN.

15:56.216 --> 15:58.870
PIE IS HOME.
PEOPLE ALWAYS COME HOME.

15:58.914 --> 16:00.785
COME ON, DIGBY.
LET'S BAKE SOME PIES.

16:00.829 --> 16:01.961
[ WHIMPERS ]

16:06.574 --> 16:08.532
WHY WON'T HE DO ANYTHING
ABOUT THIS?

16:08.576 --> 16:09.881
I DON'T KNOW.

16:09.925 --> 16:11.883
HE'S BEEN ACTING STRANGE
SINCE YESTERDAY.

16:11.927 --> 16:13.320
DOES HE SEEM DISTANT
TO YOU?

16:14.408 --> 16:16.584
WOULD YOU LIKE TO DISCUSS
HIS FEAR OF INTIMACY,

16:16.627 --> 16:19.021
HIS DARK MOODS, THAT THING
HE DOES WHEN HE'S LYING?

16:19.065 --> 16:21.154
I CAN BE A VERY GOOD RESOURCE
FOR YOU ON NED,

16:21.197 --> 16:23.721
IF YOU DON'T MIND
ME CLAWING OUT YOUR
EYEBALLS WHILE WE TALK.

16:23.765 --> 16:24.984
REALLY?

16:25.027 --> 16:26.463
WHY DO YOU WANT ME
TO CARE?

16:26.507 --> 16:28.030
BECAUSE
YOU REALLY LIKE HIM.

16:28.074 --> 16:29.553
WOULDN'T IT JUST
ROCK 'N' ROLL

16:29.597 --> 16:31.381
IF LIKING SOMEONE MEANT
THEY HAD TO LIKE YOU BACK?

16:31.425 --> 16:33.166
OF COURSE, THAT'D BE
A DIFFERENT UNIVERSE,

16:33.209 --> 16:34.863
AND SOMETHING ELSE
WOULD PROBABLY SUCK.

16:34.906 --> 16:36.212
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:36.256 --> 16:38.127
[ COFFEE CUP CLATTERS ]

16:38.171 --> 16:40.651
REFILL?

16:40.695 --> 16:43.567
THIS ISN'T REALLY
MY SHADE OF LIPSTICK.

16:43.611 --> 16:45.569
I AM GOING TO HAVE TO
CITE YOU FOR IT.

16:45.613 --> 16:47.006
SIGHT ALL YOU WANT,
SWEETIE.

16:47.049 --> 16:48.398
I'M STANDING RIGHT HERE
IN FRONT OF YOU.

16:48.442 --> 16:50.618
MM. I DON'T THINK
YOU UNDERSTAND.

16:50.661 --> 16:53.316
ANDREW BROWN,
HEALTH INSPECTOR.

16:54.709 --> 16:57.581
EXCUSE ME, BUT DON'T YOU NEED
TO NOTIFY US FIRST?

16:57.625 --> 16:59.714
NOT IF
IT'S A SURPRISE INSPECTION.

16:59.757 --> 17:01.063
SURPRISE!

17:02.282 --> 17:04.023
WH--

17:10.812 --> 17:13.075
EFFECTIVE HAIR RESTRAINT...

17:13.119 --> 17:14.120
[ BLOWS ]

17:14.163 --> 17:16.774
...NOT WORN.

17:16.818 --> 17:20.952
LIVE ANIMAL FOUND
IN THE FACILITY'S FOOD AREA.

17:20.996 --> 17:22.302
[ WHIMPERS ]

17:26.262 --> 17:27.524
[ BARKS ]

17:27.568 --> 17:29.048
[ SCRIBBLES ]

17:30.614 --> 17:32.138
YOU NEED TO OPEN THIS.

17:32.181 --> 17:33.965
WAIT. I CAN EXPLAIN
WHAT'S IN THERE.

17:34.009 --> 17:36.533
UH...NO, I CAN'T. BUT YOU SHOULD
DEFINITELY WAIT ANYWAY.

17:36.577 --> 17:38.753
IT'S OKAY.
WE NEVER USE THIS ROOM.

17:38.796 --> 17:40.102
YES, WE DO.

17:40.146 --> 17:41.973
IDO -- SOMETIMES.

17:42.017 --> 17:43.627
OPEN THE DOOR.

17:43.671 --> 17:44.759
PLEASE.

17:44.802 --> 17:46.717
[ SIGHS ]

17:56.901 --> 17:58.251
OH!

17:58.294 --> 18:00.122
Narrator:
OLIVE SNOOK WAS UNAWARE

18:00.166 --> 18:02.820
THAT THE PIE MAKER COULD BRING
DEAD FRUIT BACK TO LIFE

18:02.864 --> 18:04.257
FOR HIS PIES.

18:04.300 --> 18:07.129
WHY IS THIS ROOM FILLED
WITH ROTTEN FRUIT?

18:13.179 --> 18:15.006
THAT INSPECTION
WAS NO ACCIDENT.

18:15.050 --> 18:17.008
WE ARE BEING ATTACKED
BY A VICIOUS NUTBAG.

18:17.052 --> 18:19.010
WE NEED TO RETALIATE

18:19.054 --> 18:20.838
WITH A SWIFT AND OVERWHELMING
SHOW OF FORCE.

18:20.882 --> 18:22.492
I DON'T RETALIATE.
I'M NOT A RETALIATOR.

18:22.536 --> 18:24.059
YOU LET YOUR EMOTIONS
GET AWAY FROM YOU,

18:24.103 --> 18:25.234
AND EVERYTHING FALLS APART.

18:25.278 --> 18:27.106
YOU REALLY BELIEVE THAT,
DON'T YOU?

18:27.149 --> 18:28.629
YES.
I'VE SEEN IT HAPPEN.

18:28.672 --> 18:30.021
SHE'S COMING TO GET US.

18:30.065 --> 18:32.023
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

18:32.067 --> 18:34.504
NOBODY'S COMING
TO GET ANYBODY.

18:34.548 --> 18:35.984
BUT SHE IS.

18:38.552 --> 18:40.771
[ KNOCK ON GLASS ]

18:44.384 --> 18:45.689
YEAH?

18:45.733 --> 18:47.038
WE NEED TO TALK.

18:47.082 --> 18:49.258
YOU'RE NOT WELCOME HERE.

18:49.302 --> 18:50.694
OF COURSE SHE IS.
ALL ARE WELCOME.

18:50.738 --> 18:53.349
UH, WOULD YOU LIKE
A SLICE OF TRIPLE BERRY?

18:53.393 --> 18:54.611
OH, THANK YOU.

18:54.655 --> 18:56.613
YOU TEACH ME SOMETHING,
PIE BAKER.

18:56.657 --> 18:57.875
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:57.919 --> 18:59.442
OLIVE.

19:01.314 --> 19:02.315
[ PLATE CLANKS ]

19:05.231 --> 19:07.972
I WANTED TO APOLOGIZE
FOR MY OUTBURST YESTERDAY.

19:08.016 --> 19:09.713
IT WAS INAPPROPRIATE.

19:09.757 --> 19:11.193
THANK YOU.

19:11.237 --> 19:12.455
AND I'M SORRY FOR PRETENDING
TO BE A STUTTERER.

19:12.499 --> 19:13.630
Chuck:
YOU WERE PRETENDING?

19:13.674 --> 19:15.893
THAT'S MEAN,
AND IT'S DISRESPECTFUL.

19:15.937 --> 19:17.634
I LIKE TO MISLEAD
MY COMPETITION --

19:17.678 --> 19:19.332
ENCOURAGE UNDERESTIMATION

19:19.375 --> 19:21.072
WITH THE IDEA
THAT I HAVE AN IMPEDIMENT.

19:21.116 --> 19:22.770
BUT I KNOW THAT STUTTERING
CAN BE A VERY SERIOUS DISORDER,

19:22.813 --> 19:25.642
AND I ONLY CHOSE TO MIMIC IT
BECAUSE I'M LEGALLY BLIND.

19:25.686 --> 19:27.209
SHE'S DOING IT
AGAIN.

19:27.253 --> 19:28.515
YOU NEED TO LEAVE.

19:28.558 --> 19:29.951
OH, COME ON.

19:29.994 --> 19:31.344
WE ALL KNOW THAT THE WORLD
OF SMALL BUSINESS

19:31.387 --> 19:33.607
IS NOTHING
BUT A BIG, SEXY GAME.

19:33.650 --> 19:36.392
CALL ME OLD-FASHIONED,
BUT I LIKE TO WIN.

19:36.436 --> 19:39.090
THERE ARE PLENTY OF CUSTOMERS
FOR BOTH OF US, DILLY.

19:39.134 --> 19:41.049
WHY CAN'T WE BOTHWIN?

19:41.092 --> 19:42.616
BECAUSE I LIKE YOUR CRUST ROOF,
YOUR SQUARE FOOTAGE,

19:42.659 --> 19:44.270
AND YOUR CORNER LOCATION,

19:44.313 --> 19:47.098
EVEN IF YOUR SIGN DOES
GO ON THE FRITZ NOW AND THEN.

19:47.142 --> 19:50.711
OH, AND I WAS SO, SO SORRY
TO HEAR ABOUT YOUR INSPECTION.

19:50.754 --> 19:53.844
YOU DIDN'T COME HERE
TO APOLOGIZE AT ALL, DID YOU?

19:53.888 --> 19:57.370
NO. I CAME BY TO TELL YOU
THAT IT'S ONLY GONNA GET WORSE.

19:57.413 --> 19:58.675
YOU'VE SHOWN YOURSELF

19:58.719 --> 20:00.329
TO BE VULNERABLE
AND CARELESS COMPETITORS,

20:00.373 --> 20:02.418
SO YOU CAN COUNT
ON MORE SURPRISE INSPECTIONS

20:02.462 --> 20:04.246
AND DISRUPTIONS
TO YOUR BUSINESS.

20:04.290 --> 20:05.943
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS
TO US?

20:05.987 --> 20:08.337
WHAT I SEE, I WANT.
WHAT I WANT, I TAKE.

20:08.381 --> 20:10.600
NOTHING SCARES ME.

20:10.644 --> 20:12.646
I'VE LOOKED DEATH IN THE EYE
AND SURVIVED

20:12.689 --> 20:14.517
TO OPEN
A SUCCESSFUL CANDY FRANCHISE.

20:14.561 --> 20:15.736
CAN YOU SAY THAT?

20:15.779 --> 20:17.041
ACTUALLY, YES.

20:17.085 --> 20:19.043
NOT THE "CANDY FRANCHISE"
PART, BUT --

20:19.087 --> 20:21.132
Ned: I WON'T LET YOU BULLY ME
INTO A FIGHT, DILLY.

20:21.176 --> 20:22.786
THAT'S NOT
HOW I SETTLE THINGS.

20:22.830 --> 20:24.223
THEN YOU'LL LOSE.

20:24.266 --> 20:26.268
THANKS FOR THE PIE.

20:30.490 --> 20:33.406
WHAT IS UP
WITH THAT...WITCH?

20:33.449 --> 20:36.278
Narrator: WHAT WAS UP
WITH THAT WITCH WAS THIS --

20:36.322 --> 20:39.325
DILANIA "DILLY" BALSAM
AND BROTHER BILLY'S LIVES

20:39.368 --> 20:41.283
WERE TURNED UPSIDE DOWN

20:41.327 --> 20:43.546
WHEN THEIR PARENTS DIED
OF BIRD FLU.

20:43.590 --> 20:45.722
DILLY FELT ADRIFT,

20:45.766 --> 20:49.073
UNTIL SHE RESOLVED
TO CONFRONT HER GREATEST FEAR.

20:49.117 --> 20:51.250
SHE SET OUT ACROSS BODEGA BAY,

20:51.293 --> 20:54.296
DETERMINED TO LOOK
THE KILLERS OF HER PARENTS

20:54.340 --> 20:57.125
IN THEIR BEADY-EYED,
FEATHERED FACES.

20:57.168 --> 21:00.476
THEN, JUST AS SHE WAS
ABOUT TO REACH THE OTHER SIDE,

21:00.520 --> 21:02.304
HER WORST NIGHTMARE.

21:02.348 --> 21:05.394
[ SCREAMING ]

21:08.354 --> 21:11.052
Narrator: DILLY BALSAM
SURVIVED THE ATTACK,

21:11.095 --> 21:13.315
TO BE RESCUED
BY A LOCAL MERCHANT,

21:13.359 --> 21:16.579
WHO OFFERED HER
A VERY SWEET TREAT.

21:16.623 --> 21:20.844
SHE REALIZED THAT HER LOVE
OF TAFFY AND FEAR OF NOTHING

21:20.888 --> 21:23.630
WOULD SERVE HER WELL
IN BUSINESS.

21:23.673 --> 21:28.330
AND BALSAM'S BITTERSWEETS
TAFFY & SWEETS EMPORIUM

21:28.374 --> 21:29.853
WAS BORN.

21:33.901 --> 21:35.642
[ LEATHER CREAKING ]

21:37.078 --> 21:38.645
WHAT?

21:40.386 --> 21:43.171
YOU THINK
I SHOULD DO SOMETHING.

21:43.214 --> 21:44.694
WE'RE JUST SAYING.KIND OF.

21:44.738 --> 21:46.348
Ned: NO.

21:46.392 --> 21:47.915
YOU LET YOUR ANGER WIN
AND YOU ENGAGE THE CRAZY PERSON,

21:47.958 --> 21:49.351
THEN YOU'RE NO DIFFERENT
THAN THEY ARE.

21:49.395 --> 21:51.048
PEOPLE SAY,
"HEY. LOOK AT THAT.

21:51.092 --> 21:52.963
THERE'S TWO CRAZY PEOPLE
FIGHTING."

21:53.007 --> 21:54.051
I WILL NOT ENGAGE.

21:54.095 --> 21:56.053
YEAH,
BUT IF YOU DON'T ENGAGE,

21:56.097 --> 21:57.359
PRETTY SOON,
PEOPLE WILL START SAYING,

21:57.403 --> 21:59.361
"HEY,
LOOK AT THAT CRAZY PERSON

21:59.405 --> 22:01.015
EATING THAT GUY
JUST SITTING THERE,
DOING NOTHING."

22:01.058 --> 22:03.234
WE'VE GOT TO GIVE HER
A DOSE OF HER OWN MEDICINE.

22:03.278 --> 22:05.585
CHUCK, DON'T GO OVER
TO THE DARK SIDE.

22:05.628 --> 22:06.890
REVENGE NEVER WORKS.

22:06.934 --> 22:08.457
[ GROANS ]

22:10.285 --> 22:12.331
I GOT TO GO.

22:13.723 --> 22:15.464
ME TOO.

22:18.728 --> 22:20.904
WELL,
THIS CAN'T END WELL.

22:20.948 --> 22:22.558
[ NEWSPAPER SNAPS ]

22:26.475 --> 22:28.085
Olive: WAIT!

22:28.129 --> 22:29.739
DIDN'T THINK
YOU'D DO THIS.

22:29.783 --> 22:32.133
THOUGHT YOU WERE ALL GOODY-GOOD,
APPLE PIE, AND BASEBALL.

22:32.176 --> 22:34.396
WELL, ONLY INSOFAR AS I KNOW
HOW TO USE A BASEBALL BAT

22:34.440 --> 22:36.485
TO MAKE SOMEONE'S FACE
LOOKLIKE AN APPLE PIE.

22:40.924 --> 22:42.230
I AM SORRY ABOUT NED.

22:42.273 --> 22:44.145
WELL, NOT ABOUT NED,
BUT ABOUT UPSETTING YOU.

22:44.188 --> 22:45.799
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE OKAY ABOUT IT.

22:45.842 --> 22:47.366
SO DID I.

22:48.541 --> 22:51.152
Go, go, go, go, go,
go, go, go, go!

22:51.195 --> 22:53.067
[ BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY ]

22:53.110 --> 22:55.156
Here's what
we're notgonna do.

22:55.199 --> 22:56.723
We're not gonna start
with all this puppy-dog-face,

22:56.766 --> 22:58.638
"get back on your horse
and find a man" crapola.

22:58.681 --> 23:01.031
'Cause maybe you forgot,
but Ned was the horse
and you pushed me off.

23:01.075 --> 23:02.903
So maybe, just maybe,
I need to get a little angry

23:02.946 --> 23:04.339
before I can be
all happy about it.

23:04.383 --> 23:06.123
Okay. I get it.

23:06.167 --> 23:07.298
Thank you.

23:10.954 --> 23:12.695
THERE'S NO ALARM SYSTEM.
GOT A CREDIT CARD?

23:12.739 --> 23:14.175
WHY? YOU KNOW
HOW TO PICK A LOCK?

23:14.218 --> 23:17.352
NO. YOU'RE GONNA NEED TO PAY
FOR THE DAMAGES.

23:17.396 --> 23:19.093
HUH?

23:21.704 --> 23:23.227
COOL.

23:23.271 --> 23:24.403
COME ON!

23:30.234 --> 23:31.671
HERE.

23:33.586 --> 23:34.717
YOU READY?

23:34.761 --> 23:35.718
FOR NED.

23:35.762 --> 23:36.937
FOR NED.

23:40.244 --> 23:42.333
[ SQUEAKING ]

23:42.377 --> 23:43.639
OH. I HATE RATS.

23:44.423 --> 23:47.556
SO DO HEALTH INSPECTORS.

23:47.600 --> 23:48.731
WE'RE DONE HERE.

23:48.775 --> 23:50.385
OH, WE'RE SO DONE.

23:50.429 --> 23:51.647
[ SQUEAKING ]

23:51.691 --> 23:52.692
[ SPLAT ]

23:52.735 --> 23:54.171
[ BUBBLING ]

24:03.529 --> 24:05.531
Both: DON'T MESS
WITH THE PIE HOs.

24:05.574 --> 24:07.358
MNH-MNH.

24:07.402 --> 24:08.751
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

24:08.795 --> 24:10.361
Narrator:
HE CLEANED FOR HOURS,

24:10.405 --> 24:12.320
YET HE COULD NOT
WIPE AWAY THE FEAR

24:12.363 --> 24:14.496
THE BATTLE
WITH BALSAM'S BITTERSWEETS...

24:14.540 --> 24:15.845
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

24:15.889 --> 24:18.239
...WOULD ONLY TURN MORE BITTER.

24:23.462 --> 24:24.419
OH!

24:24.463 --> 24:25.855
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

24:27.378 --> 24:29.903
CHUCK? I THOUGHT
YOU WERE DILLY BALSAM.

24:29.946 --> 24:32.427
WHY ARE YOU DRESSED
LIKE A CAT BURGLAR?

24:32.471 --> 24:35.038
WHY ARE YOU DRESSED
LIKE A FISHMONGER?

24:35.082 --> 24:36.344
I'M SCRUBBING
THE KITCHEN.

24:36.387 --> 24:37.650
I WAS OUT WITH OLIVE.

24:37.693 --> 24:39.913
YOU KNOW WHAT?
SHE IS REALLY GREAT.

24:39.956 --> 24:41.262
[ SIGHS ]

24:41.305 --> 24:42.611
CHUCK?

24:42.655 --> 24:45.396
SORRY. MY WHOLE BODY'S
PUMPING WITH ADRENALINE.

24:46.746 --> 24:48.530
ARE YOU UPSET WITH ME?

24:48.574 --> 24:50.227
Narrator: THE TRUTH
HE WAS HIDING FROM CHUCK

24:50.271 --> 24:52.273
WAS ONE SPOT
HE COULD NOT SCRUB OUT.

24:52.316 --> 24:54.318
WHAT'S FREAKING ME OUT
IS THE RUTHLESS WOMAN

24:54.362 --> 24:55.929
TRYING TO SHUT DOWN
THE PIE HOLE.

24:55.972 --> 24:57.278
Narrator: THIS WAS TRUE.

24:57.321 --> 24:59.149
IT HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH US.

24:59.193 --> 25:01.021
Narrator: THISWAS NOT.

25:01.064 --> 25:03.589
ARE YOU SURE YOU WOULDN'T
FEEL BETTER IF YOU JUST...

25:03.632 --> 25:05.068
FOUGHT BACK A LITTLE?

25:05.112 --> 25:06.766
WHY IS IT SO HARD
FOR YOU TO SEE

25:06.809 --> 25:09.769
THAT THE BRAVE THING HERE
IS NOTTO FIGHT BACK?

25:09.812 --> 25:12.162
WELL, IN THAT CASE, OLIVE AND I
WERE COWARDS TONIGHT.

25:12.206 --> 25:14.425
WE MAY HAVE SET LOOSE
SOME INAPPROPRIATE VERMIN.

25:14.469 --> 25:15.731
[ SIGHS ]

25:18.125 --> 25:19.953
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

25:19.996 --> 25:22.303
TO CLEAN UP ANOTHER MESS.

25:22.346 --> 25:23.304
NED.

25:23.347 --> 25:24.914
NED?

25:27.351 --> 25:30.441
Narrator: THE EXPRESSION
"LIKE A RAT IN A CANDY STORE,"

25:30.485 --> 25:33.749
THOUGH SLIGHTLY LESS POPULAR,
IS EQUALLY TRUE.

25:39.015 --> 25:43.150
AS NED CAME TO TRY TO UNDO
WHAT CHUCK AND OLIVE HAD DONE,

25:43.193 --> 25:45.500
HE FOUND NOT FIGHTING THE FIGHT

25:45.544 --> 25:48.242
WAS BECOMING MORE WORK
THAN FIGHTING IT.

25:48.285 --> 25:49.852
GROSS.

25:52.551 --> 25:53.726
OH.

25:53.769 --> 25:54.727
OH!

25:54.770 --> 25:55.815
AAH! AAH!

25:55.858 --> 25:58.557
[ GROANING ]

26:04.214 --> 26:06.565
[ BUBBLING ]

26:09.219 --> 26:11.482
[ ZAP ]OH.

26:11.526 --> 26:13.920
NOT GOOD.

26:13.963 --> 26:15.095
OH!

26:16.836 --> 26:18.446
[ MOANING ]

26:18.489 --> 26:19.621
BILLY?

26:19.665 --> 26:22.537
[ MOANING ]

26:22.581 --> 26:23.930
BILLY, WERE YOU DEAD?

26:23.973 --> 26:25.540
[ MUMBLING
INCOHERENTLY ]

26:25.584 --> 26:26.802
[ LOCKS RATTLING ]

26:26.846 --> 26:28.108
[ ZAP ]

26:28.151 --> 26:30.197
OH! WAIT.

26:30.240 --> 26:31.938
FREEZE!

26:31.981 --> 26:33.635
YOU KILLED MY BROTHER!

26:42.035 --> 26:43.471
CHUCK, THIS PLACE
IS CRAWLING WITH POLICE.

26:43.514 --> 26:44.646
YOU COULD BE RECOGNIZED.
SHE SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

26:44.690 --> 26:46.039
I'VE BEEN SAYING THAT
FOR WEEKS.

26:46.082 --> 26:48.302
I HAD TO COME.
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT.

26:48.345 --> 26:49.651
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.YES, IT IS --
IF I'D HAVE JUST LISTENED TO YOU

26:49.695 --> 26:51.044
WHEN YOU TOLD ME
NOT TO RETALIATE,

26:51.087 --> 26:52.088
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE TO CLEAN UP
ALL MY MESS.

26:52.132 --> 26:53.394
I DID A TERRIBLE THING.

26:53.437 --> 26:54.656
OKAY.
SO IT'S A LITTLE YOUR FAULT.

26:54.700 --> 26:55.831
WELL,
MAYBE NOW YOU'RE EVEN.

26:56.745 --> 26:57.877
WHAT DO YOU MEAN "EVEN"?NOTHING.

26:57.920 --> 26:59.574
WHAT HAPPENED
AT THE CANDY SHOP?

26:59.618 --> 27:01.576
I WAS COLLECTING THE RATS,
AND I WAS ABOUT TO LEAVE,

27:01.620 --> 27:04.144
WHEN I SAW BILLY DEAD
IN THE TAFFY VAT.

27:04.187 --> 27:05.362
DID YOU...

27:05.406 --> 27:06.407
YEAH.

27:06.450 --> 27:07.843
BUT HE COULDN'T TALK

27:07.887 --> 27:10.367
ON ACCOUNT OF
HIS MOUTH WAS FULL OF TAFFY.

27:10.411 --> 27:13.414
I HEARD THE POLICE,
AND I...HIM AGAIN.

27:13.457 --> 27:14.981
THEY CAUGHT ME RED-HANDED.

27:15.024 --> 27:18.680
WELL, ME AND NANCY SHREW
WILL GET YOU OUT.

27:25.469 --> 27:29.212
I MEAN, IT'S A BROAD
GENERALIZATION, BUT MY GUESS IS,

27:29.256 --> 27:30.953
AN ATTRACTIVE MAN
WHO MAKES PIES FOR A LIVING

27:30.997 --> 27:32.999
SHOULDN'T EVEN SPEND A SHORT
AMOUNT OF TIME IN PRISON.

27:33.042 --> 27:34.696
HUH?

27:34.740 --> 27:38.091
Narrator: WITHOUT THE PIE MAKER
AND WITH LITTLE TO GO ON,

27:38.134 --> 27:41.834
EMERSON COD AND CHUCK SET OUT
TO SEEK THE TRUTH.

27:42.965 --> 27:45.446
YOU GONNA...DO SOMETHING?

27:45.489 --> 27:46.926
I AMDOING SOMETHING.

27:46.969 --> 27:48.623
BUT WE CAN'T WAKE HIM UP.

27:48.667 --> 27:51.365
I KNOW THAT.
DON'T YOU THINK I KNOW THAT?

27:51.408 --> 27:52.888
I'M JUST SAYING.

27:52.932 --> 27:55.282
IT'S BEEN A WHILE SINCE
YOU SOLVED A CRIME FOR REAL --

27:55.325 --> 27:57.458
YOU KNOW,
THE OLD-FASHIONED WAY.

27:57.501 --> 28:00.635
I DID FINE THE OLD-FASHIONED
WAY, AND I'D DO FINE NOW

28:00.679 --> 28:03.464
IF I COULD JUST THINK
WITHOUT YOU BLABBER-JABBERING.

28:03.507 --> 28:05.684
MM-HMM.

28:05.727 --> 28:07.773
THIS WHAT YOU DO
WHEN YOU'RE IN HERE --

28:07.816 --> 28:08.948
MUTTERING WITH THE BODIES?

28:08.991 --> 28:10.514
BICKER AND MOAN?

28:10.558 --> 28:13.779
WE WERE JUST OBSERVING THE BODY
FOR ANY, UH...

28:13.822 --> 28:15.128
VISIBLE SIGNS.

28:15.171 --> 28:17.043
I LIKE MYWAY BETTER.

28:17.086 --> 28:18.479
WHAT'S THAT?

28:18.522 --> 28:21.090
CUTTING THE SUCKER OPEN.
I GOT TO DO AN AUTOPSY.

28:21.134 --> 28:22.439
OOH!

28:22.483 --> 28:24.093
OH, GOOD.
YOU TWO CHECK UNDER THE HOOD.

28:24.137 --> 28:26.443
I'M GONNA DO A FULL BACKGROUND
CHECK ON BILLY BALSAM,

28:26.487 --> 28:28.228
SEE IF ANYBODY ELSE
WANTED TO PUT HIM

28:28.271 --> 28:30.317
IN A PERMANENT CANDY COMA.

28:30.360 --> 28:33.668
[ SAW WHIRRING ]

28:33.712 --> 28:34.887
OLIVE...

28:34.930 --> 28:36.236
[ OLIVE SOBBING ]

28:36.279 --> 28:37.716
OLIVE?

28:39.848 --> 28:41.284
[ TAP ON GLASS ]

28:41.328 --> 28:42.808
OLIVE, IT'S OKAY.

28:42.851 --> 28:44.505
[ SQUEAKS ]

28:44.548 --> 28:46.681
I BROUGHT YOU A PIE.

28:46.725 --> 28:48.552
THANK YOU.

28:48.596 --> 28:50.859
IT HAS
A SPECIAL FILLING.

28:57.736 --> 28:59.825
PLEASE TAKE THAT AWAY.

28:59.868 --> 29:01.435
OH!

29:02.653 --> 29:04.786
[ SOBBING ]

29:04.830 --> 29:07.267
Narrator: AS OLIVE CONSIDERED
HOW THE INCH-THICK GLASS

29:07.310 --> 29:09.791
PREVENTED HER FROM HOLDING
THE MAN SHE STILL LOVED,

29:09.835 --> 29:12.359
SHE REALIZED
THAT FOR THE PIE MAKER,

29:12.402 --> 29:16.102
THERE MIGHT ALWAYS BE AN
INVISIBLE BARRIER BETWEEN THEM.

29:16.145 --> 29:18.060
NO KNOWN ENEMIES?

29:18.104 --> 29:20.019
WELL, THAT'S NOT GOOD.

29:20.062 --> 29:22.369
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA BELIEVE
WHAT WE SAW AT THE AU--

29:22.412 --> 29:23.631
HOW DID YOU KNOW?

29:23.674 --> 29:24.632
GOT IT.

29:24.675 --> 29:26.025
HOW'D I KNOW WHAT?

29:26.068 --> 29:27.156
ABOUT THE FINGER.

29:27.200 --> 29:28.375
OH, I LEARNED IT
EARLY ON.

29:28.418 --> 29:29.855
SEE,
IT'S SORT OF THE UNIVERSAL

29:29.898 --> 29:32.292
"HUSH UP,
I'M ON THE DAMN PHONE" SYMBOL.

29:32.335 --> 29:33.815
OH, WELL,
IT MUST ALSO BE

29:33.859 --> 29:35.512
THE "BILLY BALSAM BIT OFF
HIS KILLER'S FINGER,

29:35.556 --> 29:37.297
'CAUSE WE FOUND IT
IN HIS STOMACH AT
THE AUTOPSY" SYMBOL.

29:37.340 --> 29:39.125
A REAL FINGER?
UH-HUH.

29:39.168 --> 29:40.822
GOOD -- ALL WE GOT TO DO
IS LIFT A PRINT OFF THAT FINGER

29:40.866 --> 29:42.476
AND MATCH IT TO WHO DONE IT
AND GET OUR BOY OUT THE SLAMMER.

29:42.519 --> 29:44.217
THERE'S NO FINGERPRINT.

29:44.260 --> 29:45.914
THE GASTRIC ACID IN HIS STOMACH
ATE AWAY AT THE SKIN,

29:45.958 --> 29:47.176
ERASED ANY TRACE
OF A PRINT.

29:47.220 --> 29:48.917
POLICE SAY
THE TRAIL'S GONE COLD.

29:48.961 --> 29:51.311
SO WHOEVER KILLED BILLY
IS WALKING AROUND
WITH NINE FINGERS,

29:51.354 --> 29:53.008
THINKING
THEY GOT AWAY WITH MURDER.

29:53.052 --> 29:54.705
MM-HMM.
FOOTLOOSE AND FINGER-FREE.

29:56.142 --> 29:57.970
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER CONSIDERED

29:58.013 --> 30:00.450
HOW NOT TELLING CHUCK
THE TRUTH ABOUT HER FATHER

30:00.494 --> 30:03.192
WAS A LOT LIKE
BEING LOCKED IN A PRISON.

30:03.236 --> 30:05.934
THEN HE CONSIDERED
HOW BEING LOCKED IN A PRISON

30:05.978 --> 30:10.896
WAS ACTUALLY MUCH WORSE THAN
SOME SILLY METAPHOR ABOUT TRUTH.

30:10.939 --> 30:13.507
HEY, BAKER BOY.
YOU GOT A NEW ROOMMATE.

30:16.249 --> 30:17.598
BURLY BRUCE?

30:17.641 --> 30:19.600
AREN'T YOU THE GUY
WHO GOT ME LOCKED UP?!

30:19.643 --> 30:21.776
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER
WAS SURPRISED THAT HERE,

30:21.820 --> 30:24.910
PERHAPS 30 SECONDS
FROM HIS OWN VIOLENT DEATH,

30:24.953 --> 30:27.347
THERE WERE NO GRAND REVELATIONS,

30:27.390 --> 30:29.262
BUT RATHER
ONLY ONE SIMPLE THOUGHT.

30:29.305 --> 30:30.306
CHUCK.

30:30.350 --> 30:31.873
IT ISYOU.

30:31.917 --> 30:34.833
Narrator: BUT IT WAS THE THOUGHT
THAT SAVED HIS LIFE.

30:34.876 --> 30:37.836
YOU KNOW, YOU NEVER TOLD ME
HOW YOU MET YOUR GIRLFRIEND.

30:37.879 --> 30:39.838
SHEILA, RIGHT?

30:42.057 --> 30:43.189
IT'S A FUNNY STORY.

30:44.712 --> 30:46.105
WE MET CARPOOLING.

30:46.148 --> 30:47.976
I WAS TIRED OF BEING STUCK
IN TRAFFIC ALL THE TIME.

30:48.020 --> 30:50.805
RULE IS, YOU NEED TWO OR MORE
FOR THE DIAMOND LANE,

30:50.849 --> 30:53.677
SO I ANSWERED A PERSONAL AD
IN A MAGAZINE.

30:53.721 --> 30:54.983
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

30:55.027 --> 30:56.637
NEXT THING I KNOW,
SHE'S AT MY DOOR.

30:56.680 --> 31:00.684
NOW, THE FIRST FEW WEEKS,
WE COMMUTED TOGETHER EVERY DAY.

31:00.728 --> 31:02.251
EH.
SHE NEVER SAID MUCH.

31:02.295 --> 31:04.950
THEN ONE NIGHT,
I'M FIXING DINNER AT MY PLACE,

31:04.993 --> 31:07.430
AND I THINK,
"I WONDER WHAT SHE'SDOING."

31:07.474 --> 31:09.519
SO I INVITE HER OVER.
WHAT THE HELL?

31:09.563 --> 31:11.826
I DID IT AS A FRIEND, YOU KNOW?
YOU KNOW HOW THAT IS.

31:11.870 --> 31:13.088
UH, YEAH.

31:13.132 --> 31:15.177
SOMETHING HAPPENED
AT THAT DINNER.

31:15.221 --> 31:18.659
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT WAS.
THE MAGIC OF ROMANCE, RIGHT?

31:18.702 --> 31:21.618
BUT THERE WAS DEFINITELY
A SPARK.

31:21.662 --> 31:22.924
WE HAD SO MUCH IN COMMON.

31:22.968 --> 31:24.970
WE TALKED FOR HOURS.

31:25.013 --> 31:27.059
ONE THING LED TO ANOTHER,
AND BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,

31:27.102 --> 31:28.582
SHE WAS BASICALLY
LIVING WITH ME.

31:28.625 --> 31:30.105
I LOVE HER SO MUCH.

31:30.149 --> 31:32.499
THAT'S WHY I TOOK THE FALL
FOR HER.

31:32.542 --> 31:34.066
I KNOW YOU LOVE SHEILA,
BRUCE,

31:34.109 --> 31:36.024
BUT MAYBE THIS IS A CHANCE
TO MOVE ON,

31:36.068 --> 31:39.114
FIND SOMEONE...
FULL OF LIFE.

31:39.158 --> 31:41.160
NO.
SHEILA'S MY GIRLFRIEND.

31:41.203 --> 31:43.989
I DON'T CARE IF THEY DON'T
PAROLE ME FOR 80 YEARS.

31:44.032 --> 31:45.555
I'LL FIND HER AGAIN.

31:45.599 --> 31:48.167
Narrator: THE TRUTH COULD KNOCK
ALL IT WANTED,

31:48.210 --> 31:50.734
BUT BURLY BRUCE
WOULD NEVER OPEN THE DOOR.

31:50.778 --> 31:53.259
AND MAYBE THAT WAS FOR THE BEST.

31:53.302 --> 31:56.392
I'M SURE SHEILA WILL
STILL BE THERE, BRUCE,
WAITING FOR YOU.

31:59.743 --> 32:04.313
Narrator: 17 MILES AWAY,
THE SEARCH TO FINGER

32:04.357 --> 32:08.013
THE FINGERLESS KILLER
OF BILLY BALSAM CONTINUED.

32:08.056 --> 32:09.971
NO MISSING-DIGIT EMERGENCIES
REPORTED

32:10.015 --> 32:12.060
AT ANY OF THE LOCAL HOSPITALS
LAST NIGHT.

32:12.104 --> 32:14.106
MAYBE THE KILLER DIDN'T REALIZE
THEY LOST A FINGER,

32:14.149 --> 32:15.890
SO THEY NEVER REPORTED IT
TO THE HOSPITAL.

32:15.934 --> 32:17.152
HEY, YEAH.

32:17.196 --> 32:18.414
THAT WOULD NARROW
OUR LIST OF SUSPECTS

32:18.458 --> 32:19.850
DOWN TO ONLY
INSANELY STUPID PEOPLE.

32:19.894 --> 32:21.591
SOME AMPUTEES HAVE
PHANTOM LIMBS.

32:21.635 --> 32:23.942
THEY THINK THE SEVERED
BODY PART IS STILL THERE,

32:23.985 --> 32:25.465
EVEN WHEN IT'S NOT.

32:25.508 --> 32:27.249
IT'S LIKE A PSYCHOLOGICAL
PROTECTION MECHANISM

32:27.293 --> 32:28.947
TO SAVE THEM
FROM THE TRAUMA.

32:28.990 --> 32:30.513
[ SNORES ]

32:30.557 --> 32:32.776
WE NEED TO GO BACK
TO BITTERSWEETS.

32:32.820 --> 32:34.778
WE NEED TO GET INTO
THE SCENE OF THE CRIME.

32:34.822 --> 32:37.651
HOW ARE WE GONNA
GET PAST DILLY?

32:41.046 --> 32:42.351
HIYA.

32:42.395 --> 32:45.398
YOU GOT A LOT OF SPUNK
COMING BACK HERE.

32:45.441 --> 32:47.269
I'M SURPRISED
YOU'REHERE.

32:47.313 --> 32:49.576
YEAH, WELL,
IT'S WHAT BILLY WOULD WANT.

32:49.619 --> 32:51.970
CAN I TALK TO YOU FOR A SECOND
IN PRIVATE?

32:53.928 --> 32:56.148
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

32:57.323 --> 33:00.195
I MEAN OUTSIDEPRIVATE --
OUTSIDE.

33:00.239 --> 33:02.545
I KNOW THIS HAS BEEN
SO HARD FOR YOU,

33:02.589 --> 33:04.678
AND I FEEL YOUR PAIN.

33:04.721 --> 33:07.246
IT'S --
DEATH IS THE WORST.

33:13.165 --> 33:16.211
THIS DUDE BIT OFF
SOMEBODY'S FINGER

33:16.255 --> 33:20.650
AND WAS FOUND FACEUP
IN THIS TAFFY.

33:20.694 --> 33:22.000
WHICH MEANS...

33:22.043 --> 33:24.263
HE PROBABLY WASN'T ATTACKED
FROM BEHIND.

33:24.306 --> 33:25.612
RIGHT.

33:25.655 --> 33:27.309
SO THERE MUST HAVE BEEN
A STRUGGLE.

33:27.353 --> 33:31.096
I'D SAY MORE LIKE
A FULL-ON BRAWL.

33:31.139 --> 33:32.314
HMM?

33:32.358 --> 33:33.924
THIS TABLE WAS MOVED.

33:33.968 --> 33:35.883
OH.

33:37.580 --> 33:40.061
Emerson: [ CLEARS THROAT ]
WRONG KITCHEN.

33:40.105 --> 33:42.281
YOU KNOW, MARBLE'S
A VERY INTERESTING STONE.

33:42.324 --> 33:44.848
IT'S RESISTANT TO GREASE
AND OILS, WHICH LEAVE STAINS.

33:44.892 --> 33:47.503
SO, IF IT'S NOT CLEANED PROPERLY
AND RIGHT AWAY

33:47.547 --> 33:49.940
AND SOMEONE WERE TO PUT
THEIR HAND ON IT, SAY, UM...

33:49.984 --> 33:52.595
IN THE HEAT
OF A SCUFFLE...

33:52.639 --> 33:55.511
THEN THE OILS
ON THEIR HANDS SHOULD...

33:55.555 --> 33:56.817
[ BLOWS ]

33:56.860 --> 33:59.298
...LEAVE IMPRINTS
ON THE SURFACE.

33:59.341 --> 34:00.342
HUH.

34:06.392 --> 34:07.958
TWO HANDS.

34:08.002 --> 34:09.482
NINE FINGERPRINTS.

34:09.525 --> 34:12.050
ONE TAFFY-DROWNING
MURDERER.

34:12.093 --> 34:13.964
Olive:
I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW

34:14.008 --> 34:15.923
THAT EVEN THOUGH
WE GOT OFF ON THE WRONG FOOT,

34:15.966 --> 34:18.143
WE ARE STILL YOUR NEIGHBORS,
AND WE ARE HERE FOR YOU.

34:18.186 --> 34:20.145
AND I REALIZE
WE MAY NOT BE ABLE TO SMILE

34:20.188 --> 34:21.842
AND WAVE AT EACH OTHER
FOR A WHILE

34:21.885 --> 34:23.713
BECAUSE OF EVENTS
THAT HAVE OCCURRED.

34:23.757 --> 34:25.150
YEAH, I BROKE YOUR SIGN

34:25.193 --> 34:26.847
AND CALLED THE CITY
HEALTH INSPECTOR HOTLINE,

34:26.890 --> 34:28.196
AND YOU ALL
KILLED MY BROTHER.

34:28.240 --> 34:31.156
SO WE AGREE TO DISAGREE
ON THAT.

34:37.510 --> 34:38.815
DO YOU WANT PROOF?

34:38.859 --> 34:40.208
DO YOU WANT ME
TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING

34:40.252 --> 34:41.514
THAT PROVES EXACTLY
WHAT HAPPENED TO BILLY?

34:41.557 --> 34:42.863
LET ME SHOW YOU.

34:42.906 --> 34:44.082
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

34:46.780 --> 34:48.173
WHAT?
IT'S AN EMPTY CAR TRUNK.

34:48.216 --> 34:49.348
NO, IT'S NOT.

34:49.391 --> 34:51.089
AAAAAAAH!

34:55.919 --> 34:57.486
[ BANGING ]HELP! HELP!

35:03.797 --> 35:07.017
Her hands --
she's wearing mittens.

35:07.061 --> 35:08.758
PUT THE GUN DOWN, LADY.

35:08.802 --> 35:11.021
THE PIE-MAKING MURDERER
COULDN'T FINISH THE JOB,

35:11.065 --> 35:13.589
SO HE SENT HIS GIRLFRIEND
AND THE MUSCLE TO FINISH ME OFF?

35:13.633 --> 35:15.504
NED DIDN'T KILL ANYONE,
AND YOU KNOW IT.

35:15.548 --> 35:17.463
WE'RE JUST TRYING
TO FIND OUT THE TRUTH.

35:17.506 --> 35:21.075
THE ONLY TRUTH YOU NEED TO KNOW
IS I MISS MY BROTHER.

35:26.776 --> 35:28.561
HEY,
YOU GOT 10 FINGERS.

35:28.604 --> 35:30.171
YOU'RE NOT THE KILLER.

35:30.215 --> 35:32.391
AND I DON'T THINK
YOU WANT TO BEONE, EITHER.

35:32.434 --> 35:35.089
LET US TAKE THE EVIDENCE
TO THE AUTHORITIES.

35:35.133 --> 35:37.744
WE'LL FIND OUT
WHO REALLY KILLED YOUR BROTHER.

35:43.619 --> 35:44.968
ALL RIGHT. YOU CAN GO.

35:45.012 --> 35:47.493
[ SIGHS ]

35:47.536 --> 35:50.235
IF YOU CAN PUT WHOEVER
KILLED MY BROTHER BEHIND BARS,

35:50.278 --> 35:51.584
I WILL BE HAPPY.

35:51.627 --> 35:53.151
I THOUGHT I WANTED REVENGE,

35:53.194 --> 35:56.502
BUT ALL I REALLY NEED
IS J-J-J-JUSTICE.

35:59.026 --> 36:00.767
DID SHE JUST STUTTER?

36:00.810 --> 36:03.335
Emerson: YEP.

36:03.378 --> 36:05.685
AND TAKE YOUR TRUNK MONKEY
WITH YOU.

36:05.728 --> 36:06.903
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

36:06.947 --> 36:09.079
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

36:09.123 --> 36:12.518
AFTER OLIVE WAS FREED
FROM DILLY BALSAM'S TRUNK...

36:12.561 --> 36:14.563
STINKS IN THERE.

36:14.607 --> 36:16.913
Narrator:
...THE AUTHORITIES EXPLAINED
THAT THE TIME IT WOULD TAKE

36:16.957 --> 36:18.567
FOR THE DISMEMBERED DIGIT

36:18.611 --> 36:21.483
TO PASS THROUGH THE DIGESTIVE
SYSTEM OF BILLY BALSAM

36:21.527 --> 36:23.398
AND HAVE ITS FINGERPRINTS ERASED

36:23.442 --> 36:25.879
BY THE ACID
CONTAINED IN THE STOMACH

36:25.922 --> 36:28.534
PUT THE TIME OF DEATH
OF ONE BILLY BALSAM

36:28.577 --> 36:31.667
HOURS EARLIER THAN THE TIME
THE PIE MAKER WAS FOUND

36:31.711 --> 36:33.234
HOVERING OVER THE BODY.

36:33.278 --> 36:36.019
FINGERPRINT ANALYSIS
OF THE SHEET OF CANDY FRUIT

36:36.063 --> 36:37.934
EXPOSED
THE NINE-FINGERED CULPRIT

36:37.978 --> 36:39.371
TO BE NONE OTHER THAN...

36:39.414 --> 36:43.723
ANDREW BROWN, HEALTH INSPECTOR,

36:43.766 --> 36:46.247
WHOM, IT WAS REVEALED
UPON FURTHER INVESTIGATION,

36:46.291 --> 36:49.598
HAD BEEN BLACKMAILING
DILLY AND BILLY BALSAM.

36:49.642 --> 36:53.254
HAVING PAID OFF THE INSPECTOR
TO CONDUCT A SURPRISE INSPECTION

36:53.298 --> 36:56.214
THAT LED TO THE PIE HOLE'S
TEMPORARY SHUTDOWN,

36:56.257 --> 36:58.259
BROWN HAD DEMANDED A BRIBE,

36:58.303 --> 37:01.306
LEST HE REVEAL
BILLY AND DILLY'S DASTARDLY DEED

37:01.349 --> 37:03.221
AND SHUT THEMDOWN, TOO.

37:03.264 --> 37:06.006
UNWILLING TO BE BULLIED,
BILLY BALSAM BALKED.

37:06.049 --> 37:07.355
[ CRUNCH ]

37:07.399 --> 37:08.878
AAAAAAAAH!

37:14.754 --> 37:17.147
Woman:
HEALTH INSPECTOR ANDREW BROWN
IS NOW BELIEVED

37:17.191 --> 37:19.454
TO BE THE NUMBER-ONE SUSPECT
IN THE MURDER

37:19.498 --> 37:23.676
OF BALSAM'S BITTERSWEETS
TAFFY & SWEETS EMPORIUM
CO-OWNER BILLY BALSAM.

37:23.719 --> 37:27.114
THANKS TO THE WORK OF PRIVATE
INVESTIGATOR EMERSON COD,

37:27.157 --> 37:29.769
THE OWNER OF THE LOCAL PIE HOLE
HAS BEEN CLEARED OF ALL CHARGES

37:29.812 --> 37:31.466
AND RELEASED FROM JAIL.

37:31.510 --> 37:33.120
AUTHORITIES ARE CONDUCTING
AN EXTENSIVE SEARCH

37:33.163 --> 37:35.862
FOR ANDREW BROWN,
WHO REMAINS AT LARGE.

37:35.905 --> 37:39.300
[ BELL RINGS ] UP NEXT, CAN APES DRIVE?
WE'LL FIND OUT.

37:39.344 --> 37:40.954
AAAAAAAH!AAAAAAAH!

37:40.997 --> 37:42.956
DEAD GIRL WALKING.

37:42.999 --> 37:44.784
WALKING RIGHT TOWARD ME.

37:44.827 --> 37:45.959
ARE YOU OKAY?

37:46.002 --> 37:47.047
OH.

37:47.090 --> 37:48.266
SURE.
I MEAN, I AM NOW.

37:48.309 --> 37:49.441
NED.

37:49.484 --> 37:51.965
OH. [ LAUGHS ]

37:52.008 --> 37:53.271
THAT HUG
GOES DOUBLE FOR ME.

37:53.314 --> 37:55.316
OH, DOUBLE.
DOUBLE HUG.

37:56.665 --> 37:57.840
OLIVE.

37:57.884 --> 37:58.972
WHAT?

37:59.015 --> 38:01.714
OH. [ LAUGHS ]

38:01.757 --> 38:02.976
PSST!

38:04.630 --> 38:06.371
COME ON.

38:10.679 --> 38:14.161
DOING THIS WORK
WITHOUT YOU...

38:14.204 --> 38:16.163
WELL, IT ACTUALLY
ENDS UP MEANING

38:16.206 --> 38:18.557
I'M DOING
A WHOLE LOTOF WORK.

38:18.600 --> 38:22.474
NOT THAT I CAN'T DO IT,
'CAUSE I CAN.

38:22.517 --> 38:24.084
I JUST DON'T LIKE IT.

38:24.127 --> 38:25.433
GLAD TO BE BACK.

38:25.477 --> 38:26.826
HMM.

38:26.869 --> 38:28.567
IT'S NOT ALL THAT BAD
IN JAIL.

38:28.610 --> 38:31.396
I HAD A LOT OF TIME TO THINK,
AND I CAME TO A DECISION.

38:31.439 --> 38:34.007
EVERYONE TALKS ABOUT
HOW THE TRUTH WILL SET YOU FREE,

38:34.050 --> 38:35.791
BUT BURLY BRUCE
WAS FREE TO LOVE SOMEONE

38:35.835 --> 38:37.793
'CAUSE HE WAS SO GOOD
AT LYING TO HIMSELF

38:37.837 --> 38:39.404
ABOUT THAT DOLL
BEING REAL.

38:39.447 --> 38:42.015
WHICH IS TO SAY...
"GO, LYING."

38:42.058 --> 38:46.498
OR AT LEAST "YAY
TO NOT TELLING THE TRUTH."

38:46.541 --> 38:47.586
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

38:50.545 --> 38:53.374
I'M NOT GONNA TELL CHUCK
ABOUT HER DAD.

38:53.418 --> 38:54.941
HUH?

38:54.984 --> 38:57.552
I JUST HEARD THAT AS THOUGH
IT CAME OUT OF MY OWN MOUTH.

38:57.596 --> 38:59.337
OH, WAIT. IT DID.

38:59.380 --> 39:00.990
WELL, YOU WERE RIGHT.

39:01.034 --> 39:02.340
GOOD NIGHT.

39:02.383 --> 39:03.863
GOOD NIGHT.

39:08.737 --> 39:10.913
WELCOME HOME.

39:10.957 --> 39:14.047
Narrator:
SAFELY HOME AND CLEARED
OF HAVING COMMITTED ANY CRIME,

39:14.090 --> 39:17.442
THE PIE MAKER ENJOYED
A CELEBRATORY PIECE OF PIE

39:17.485 --> 39:19.139
AND WENT UP TO BED.

39:25.798 --> 39:27.321
[ COFFEE CUP CLATTERS ]

39:33.458 --> 39:35.677
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]

39:35.721 --> 39:37.244
OLIVE.

39:37.287 --> 39:38.898
FREDO.

39:38.941 --> 39:41.204
I KNEW IT WAS YOU.

40:03.531 --> 40:06.404
Narrator:
SOMETIMES, A CRIME OF PASSION

40:06.447 --> 40:10.059
IS NOT REALIZING THE PASSION
IN TIME,

40:10.103 --> 40:15.151
WHILE OTHER TIMES, THE CRIME IS
NOT SEEING THE WORLD AS IT IS.

40:15.195 --> 40:20.635
BUT MOST CRIMES OF PASSION
AREACTUALLY A CRIME.

40:33.735 --> 40:36.477
SO, PEOPLE CAN ACTUALLY
FEEL THEIR LIMBS

40:36.521 --> 40:37.783
AFTER THEY'RE GONE.

40:37.826 --> 40:40.133
IT'S WEIRD,
BUT I KIND OF LIKE IT.

40:40.176 --> 40:41.308
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:41.351 --> 40:43.049
I KNOW. ME TOO.

40:44.833 --> 40:48.620
WHEN I WAS IN JAIL, I THINK
YOUWERE MY PHANTOM LIMB.

40:48.663 --> 40:50.970
AW. I WAS?

40:51.013 --> 40:52.493
YOU WERE.

40:52.537 --> 40:54.800
IT FELT LIKE YOU WERE WITH ME
THE WHOLE TIME.

40:54.843 --> 40:57.716
[ INHALES,
EXHALES DEEPLY ]

40:57.759 --> 41:00.414
I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE BACK.

41:00.458 --> 41:03.461
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER HAD NEVER FELT
CLOSER TO ANOTHER PERSON

41:03.504 --> 41:06.159
AS HE DID AT THAT MOMENT.

41:06.202 --> 41:08.727
HE FELT A RUSH OF EMOTION
OVERCOME HIM...

41:08.770 --> 41:09.902
CHUCK.

41:09.945 --> 41:11.294
HMM?

41:11.338 --> 41:13.166
Narrator:
...CAUSING ONE CRIME OF PASSION

41:13.209 --> 41:16.604
THAT CAME IN THE FORM
OF A CONFESSION.

41:16.648 --> 41:18.084
I KILLED YOUR DAD.
